The part of the game that is protectable is that which is tied to the
players: competitions, game collections, etc.

Publishing the moves without the name of the players is obviously fine, but
no one's ever challenged the right-to-publicity angles, i.e., Fischer's
right to publicity when they let you know he was playing White, etc.

I suspect sometime or other an organizer or player is going to assert these
rights.  Shveshnikov is about the only play I know of who has, and no one
has wanted to challenge him I guess out of fear of losing a publishing cash
cow.

How rich would Fischer be now if he were allowed to license the use of his
name in connection with his game scores?

